-@title = "#{t('txt.jqgrid.name')} #{t('txt.jqgrid.demo.name')} - #{t('txt.jqgrid.demo.v36')} - #{t('txt.jqgrid.demo.api')}"
.demo
  %h3
    =@title
  %center
    %table#invheaders_demo1401.scroll{ :cellspacing => "0", :cellpadding => "0" }
    #invheaders_demo1401_pager.scroll{ :style => "text-align:center;" }

/ End demo 
.demo-description
  %p  
    From 3.6 we introduce new API, which is similar to jQuery UI. Using the new API saves a namespace
    conflicts with other plugins and make using jqGrid more natural in the code, showing that this is connected
    with jqGrid methods. The calling convension is:
  %p
    %code
      (jqgridelement).jqGrid( method ,parameter1,...,parameterN);
    %br
    Where 
    %i
      method
    is exiting jqGrid method.
  %p
    In the example above we do:
    %br
    %code
      jQuery("#newapi").jqGrid('navGrid','#pnewapi',{edit:false,add:false,del:false});
  %p
    To enjoy full of this API a new variable is used in $.jgrid namespace - called 
    %i
      $.jgrid.no_legacy_api
    , which default value is false. The variable should be set before including jqGrid Java Script file or
    can be added in the language file.     
/ End demo-description
